tip.text: Great food and service. Had a Puller Pork Bun and local Hillbilly's Cider. Good laid back modern atmosphere. Quick turnaround allowed me to get back to my tourist couch on time too. Recommended!
It's pancakes for breakfast here sometimes. Looks awesome, but a tad too sour to me. Sunny side eggs or sandwiches are a better choice here.

tip.text: Newest addition to Klaipeda coffee scene. Standout in the city. Opened by coffee obsessed architects, hence the name. Big variety of flavors and prep types, cozy and friendly atmosphere.
Squirrels. Like tons of them. Super cute. Super aggressive. Don't forget to bring some nuts, otherwise you may not make it out alive.
Food is great, as is the service. The place to go when you are in Klaipeda. Book a table in advance though, there are like 7 of them only. Small & cozy!
